	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64183097"><p>Because it's almost as though the IRS stated the terms clearly and right there on the very page you linked to? Maybe that's the difference?</p><p><div class="quote"><p>Guided Tax Software provides free online tax preparation and filing at an IRS partner site. Our partners deliver this service at no cost to qualifying taxpayers. Taxpayers whose AGI is $79,000 or less qualify for a free federal tax return.</p></div><p><div class="quote"><p>Free File Fillable Forms are electronic federal tax forms, equivalent to a paper 1040 form. You should know how to prepare your own tax return using form instructions and IRS publications if needed. It provides a free option to taxpayers whose income (AGI) is greater than $79,000.</p></div></div>
	</div>

